one-hundred 1.0.0 API

Packages 
Package Description
com.nickbenn.onehundred
Base package for classes and interfaces making up the implementation of One Hundred.
com.nickbenn.onehundred.controller
Classes responsible for handling command-line options to initialize the system state; presenting visual representations of the system state (as constructed by the classes and interfaces in the com.nickbenn.onehundred.view package); prompting for and accepting user input; and handling user input by invoking appropriate methods on instances of model and view classes.
com.nickbenn.onehundred.controller.strategy
Throwable subclasses encapsulating errors that may occur during parsing and handling of configuration options specified during application startup.
com.nickbenn.onehundred.model
Classes and interfaces responsible for managing the internal system state, including validation and processing of moves in the game that may result in state changes.
com.nickbenn.onehundred.model.exception
Throwable subclasses encapsulating errors that may occur during initialization of the system state and during subsequent processing of state transitions (moves in the game).
com.nickbenn.onehundred.view
Classes and interfaces responsible for constructing text-based (in the current implementation) representations of the system state and key transitions.
